headline: TE Connectivity (TEL) Net Profit Margin Drops to 10.7%, Challenging Bullish Narratives
summary: TE Connectivity (TEL) reported a net profit margin of 10.7%, a significant decline from last year’s 20.2%, as the company navigated tougher year-on-year earnings and operating conditions. The company now forecasts annual earnings growth of 15.6%, just below the broader US market’s expected 15.7%, with revenue projected to rise by 7.5% per year compared to a 10.3% market estimate.
